Charter Federal Savings and LoanAssociation of Bristol, Va., said it has agreed to acquireJefferson Savings and Loan Association of Warrenton, Va.    Under terms of the transaction, which would result in a 1.3billion dlr thrift institution, stockholders of Jefferson willget 30.50 dlrs per share, half in cash and half in shares ofCharter.    The resulting association will operate under the name ofCharter and will be based in Bristol.    The transaction is valued at about 16.3 mln dlrs, aJefferson spokesman said.    Charter said the merger is subject to approval of theFederal Home Loan Bank Board.    Jefferson reported a 1.5 mln dlrs loss and assets of 360mln dlrs for the year ended September 30, 1986.    For the year ended June 30, Charter reported net income of7.9 mln dlrs. Assets totaled about 844.0 mln dlrs as ofDecember 31. Reuter&#3;